hi <@UEYV6TEAU>, we see your questions in the developer forum. <@UDDJG2VFG> replied there, but it seems like you’ve been working with <@UFBNA9K9A>. Zack can continue helping you in this channel if you want but please refrain from reposting your question everywhere across forums and channels. we will get to you in turn.

To bulk update contacts, you need to use this endpoint and format your json body correctly <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/methods/contacts/batch_create_or_update>. Please follow the docs accordingly

If you’re updating contacts you should be passing valid contact id’s or emails. Make sure you are using your own api key, *not* `hapikey=demo`. Demo should be replaced by your own api key. If you’re using *vid* to update a contact, it *must* be a valid ID. If using email addresses, you can pass one that may or may not exist in your account yet.

the request looks like this:

```[
     {
      "vid": [a valid contact id goes here],
      "properties": [
        {
          "property": "city",
          "value": "Cambridge"
        }]
        },
        {
        "email": [a valid email goes here],
        "properties": [
           {
             "property": "city",
             "value": "Cambridge"
           }]
      }
]```

You can add up to 1000 contact’s in this JSON object, but must follow the prescribed format. Please refer to the docs for more specific info
